Edition:
Quote:  <i>burl </i>or <i>birl n. Austral. & N.Z. inf. 1.</i> a ride in a car. <i>2</i>. an attempt; try (esp. in <i>give it a burl</i>). [C20: ? < BIRL in Scots sense: to spin or turn]
Notes:  [1986 NZPOD 95; 1985 Collins NZ Compact Dict. 64]



Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  50
Edition:
Quote:  <i>give it a birl/burl</i> make an attempt; from causing the coin to spin in the game of two-up; also <i>give it a go</i> and <i>give it a pop</i>; eg `If nobody else will ride the damn horse, I'll give it a birl/go/pop.' Mostly NZA.
Notes:
